data.name: RBI0000Description
data.value: An unexpected error happened while generating the code. No code will be added to the compilation.
data.comment: An optional longer localizable description of the diagnostic.

data.name: RBI0000MessageFormat
data.value: An unexpected error ocurred while processing '{0}'. Please fill a bug report at https://github.com/dotnet/macios/issues/new.
data.comment: The format-able message the diagnostic displays.

data.name: RBI0000Title
data.value: Unexpected error
data.comment: The title of the diagnostic.

data.name: RBI0001Description
data.value: In order for the code to be generated all binding types have to be declared as partial classes.

data.name: RBI0001MessageFormat
data.value: The binding type '{0}' must be declared partial
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of the class.

data.name: RBI0001Title
data.value: Binding type declaration must be partial

data.name: RBI0002Description
data.value: BindingType<Class> can only decorate partial classes.

data.name: RBI0002MessageFormat
data.value: BindingType<Class> can only be used to decorate a class but was found on '{0}' which is not a class
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of type.

data.name: RBI0002Title
data.value: BindingType<Class> must be on a class

data.name: RBI0003Description
data.value: BindingType<Category> can only decorate partial classes.

data.name: RBI0003MessageFormat
data.value: BindingType<Category> can only be used to decorate a class but was found on '{0}' which is not a class
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of type.

data.name: RBI0003Title
data.value: BindingType<Category> must be on a class

data.name: RBI0004Description
data.value: BindingType<Category> can only decorate static classes.

data.name: RBI0004MessageFormat
data.value: BindingType<Category> can only be used to decorate a static class but was found on '{0}' which is not static
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of type.

data.name: RBI0004Title
data.value: BindingType<Category> must be on a static class

data.name: RBI0005Description
data.value: BindingType<Protocol> can only decorate interfaces.

data.name: RBI0005MessageFormat
data.value: BindingType<Protocol> can only be used to decorate an interface but was found on '{0}' which is not an interface
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of type.

data.name: RBI0005Title
data.value: BindingType<Protocol> must be on an interface

data.name: RBI0006Description
data.value: BindingType can only decorate enumerators.

data.name: RBI0006MessageFormat
data.value: BindingType can only be used to decorate an enumerator but was found on '{0}' which is not an enumerator
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of type.

data.name: RBI0006Title
data.value: BindingType must be on an enumerator

data.name: RBI0007Description
data.value: BindingType<StrongDictionary> can only decorate classes.

data.name: RBI0007MessageFormat
data.value: BindingType<StrongDictionary> can only be used to decorate a class but was found on '{0}' which is not a class
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of type.

data.name: RBI0007Title
data.value: BindingType<StrongDictionary> must be on a class

data.name: RBI0008Description
data.value: In order for the code to be generated a smart enum value has to have a backing field.

data.name: RBI0008MessageFormat
data.value: The enum '{0}' must have at least one member tagged with a Field<EnumValue> attribute
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of the enumerator.

data.name: RBI0008Title
data.value: Smart enum values must have a value tagged with an Field<EnumValue> attribute

data.name: RBI0009Description
data.value: Smart enum backing field cannot appear more than once.

data.name: RBI0009MessageFormat
data.value: The backing field '{0}' for the enum value '{1}' is already in use for the enum value '{2}'
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of the enum value. '{1}' is the name of a native field. '{2}' is the previous enum value

data.name: RBI0009Title
data.value: Smart enum backing field cannot appear more than once

data.name: RBI0010Description
data.value: Smart enum backing field must be a valid identifier.

data.name: RBI0010MessageFormat
data.value: The enum value '{0}' backing field '{1}' is not a valid identifier
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of the enum value. '{1}' is the name of a native field.

data.name: RBI0010Title
data.value: Smart enum backing field must represent a valid C# identifier to be used

data.name: RBI0011Description
data.value: Smart enum backing field for a non Apple framework must provide a library name.

data.name: RBI0011MessageFormat
data.value: The field attribute for the enum value '{0}' must set the property 'LibraryName'
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of the enumerator value.

data.name: RBI0011Title
data.value: Non Apple framework bindings must provide a library name

data.name: RBI0012Description
data.value: Fields of known Apple frameworks should not provide a LibraryName.

data.name: RBI0012MessageFormat
data.value: The Field attribute for the enum value '{0}' must not provide a value for 'LibraryName'
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of the native field.

data.name: RBI0012Title
data.value: Do not provide the LibraryName for known Apple frameworks

data.name: RBI0013Description
data.value: Wrong flags were used in the FieldAttribute when applying it on an enum value.

data.name: RBI0013MessageFormat
data.value: Used attribute '{0}' on enum value '{1}' when 'ObjCBindings.FieldAttribute<ObjCBindings.EnumValue>' was expected
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of an attribute. '{1}' is the name of the enumerator value.

data.name: RBI0013Title
data.value: Enum values must be tagged with Field<EnumValue>

data.name: RBI0014Description
data.value: Native object accessed by handle must be kept alive, either implicitly by access or through GC.KeepAlive.

data.name: RBI0014MessageFormat
data.value: Variable '{0}' has its Handle property accessed but is not kept alive later in the method
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of the variable.

data.name: RBI0014Title
data.value: INativeObject not kept alive after Handle access

data.name: RBI0015Description
data.value: With the provided binding flags in the export methods, the mentioned field cannot be null.

data.name: RBI0015MessageFormat
data.value: Field '{0}' is required when one of the following flags is set: '{1}'
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of the field and '{1}' is a comma separated list of flags

data.name: RBI0015Title
data.value: Field value cannot be null

data.name: RBI0016Description
data.value: The fields are mutually exclusive which means that at most one of them can be set.

data.name: RBI0016MessageFormat
data.value: Fields '{0}' must be mutually exclusive, at most one field can be set
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of the fields.

data.name: RBI0016Title
data.value: Fields are mutually exclusive

data.name: RBI0017Description
data.value: The field is only allowed when a specific flag is used.

data.name: RBI0017MessageFormat
data.value: Fields '{0}' was set with flag {1} when is only allowed with flag {2}
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of the field, {1} is the flag type found and {2} is the flag we should have

data.name: RBI0017Title
data.value: Field used with the wrong flag

data.name: RBI0018Description
data.value: The export attribute must have a nonnull selector.

data.name: RBI0018MessageFormat
data.value: An export property selector must not contain any whitespace

data.name: RBI0018Title
data.value: Null selector

data.name: RBI0019Description
data.value: The selector string cannot contain any whitespace characters.

data.name: RBI0019MessageFormat
data.value: An export property selector must not contain any whitespace

data.name: RBI0019Title
data.value: Bad selector format

data.name: RBI0020Description
data.value: The named parameter is only allowed with a specific flag.

data.name: RBI0020MessageFormat
data.value: The '{0}' named parameter can only be used when '{1}' has been set
data.comment: '{0}' is the name of the field and {1} is the name of the flag.

data.name: RBI0020Title
data.value: Invalid named parameter

data.name: RBI0021Description
data.value: The flag combination is not allowed.

data.name: RBI0021MessageFormat
data.value: The combination of flags {0} is not allowed
data.comment: '{0}' is the list of flags that cannot be combined.

data.name: RBI0021Title
data.value: Invalid flag

data.name: RBI0022Description
data.value: The export attribute must have a nonnull selector.

data.name: RBI0022MessageFormat
data.value: The export attribute must have a nonnull or empty selector

data.name: RBI0022Title
data.value: Null selector

data.name: RBI0023Description
data.value: The selector string cannot contain any whitespace characters.

data.name: RBI0023MessageFormat
data.value: An export method selector must not contain any whitespace

data.name: RBI0023Title
data.value: Bad selector format

data.name: RBI0024Description
data.value: The native prefix/suffix cannot have white spaces.

data.name: RBI0024MessageFormat
data.value: The {0} string must not contain any whitespace
data.comment: The {0} is the name of the field.

data.name: RBI0024Title
data.value: Bad native prefix/suffix

data.name: RBI0025Description
data.value: Names of types to be generated cannot have white spaces.

data.name: RBI0025MessageFormat
data.value: The {0} type name must not contain any whitespace
data.comment: The {0} is the name of the field.

data.name: RBI0025Title
data.value: Bad type name

data.name: RBI0026Description
data.value: The async method name cannot have white spaces.

data.name: RBI0026MessageFormat
data.value: The async method name must not contain any whitespace

data.name: RBI0026Title
data.value: Bad method name

data.name: RBI0027Description
data.value: The symbol is accessible in a platform where it is not supported..

data.name: RBI0027MessageFormat
data.value: The symbol '{0}' is accessible on platform '{1}' when it was marked otherwise
data.comment: The {0} is the name of the enum, property or method, {1} is the name of the platform.

data.name: RBI0027Title
data.value: Bad method name

data.name: RBI0028Description
data.value: A flag value was used on an attribute that does not support it and will be ignored.

data.name: RBI0028MessageFormat
data.value: The flag '{0}' is no supported on '{1}' and will be ignored
data.comment: The {0} is the name of the flag, {1} is the name of the attribute.

data.name: RBI0028Title
data.value: Ignored fflag

data.name: RBI0029Description
data.value: There is a mismatch between the arguments of a method/property and the number of ':' in a selector.

data.name: RBI0029MessageFormat
data.value: There is a mismatch between the arguments of '{0}' (found {1}) and the selector '{2}' (found {3})
data.comment: The {0} is the name of the method or property, {1} is the argument count. {2} is the selector and {3} is its argument count

data.name: RBI0029Title
data.value: Selector argument mismatch

data.name: RBI0030Description
data.value: Field properties must be declared static.

data.name: RBI0030MessageFormat
data.value: Field properties must be declared static

data.name: RBI0030Title
data.value: Wrong field declaration

data.name: RBI0031Description
data.value: Exported properties must be declared partial.

data.name: RBI0031MessageFormat
data.value: Exported properties must be declared partial

data.name: RBI0031Title
data.value: Wrong property declaration
